dcMgmdMib.name: dcMgmdMib

revisions.description: Added mgmdPmStaticGroupStorageType for MCAST FQDN feature

dcMgmdMib.description: The MIB module for management of the MGMD product.

NonZeroUnsigned8.name: NonZeroUnsigned8
NonZeroUnsigned8.description: An non-zero unsigned32 further restricted to 8 Bits.

AdminStatus.name: AdminStatus
AdminStatus.description: The desired administrative state of a MGMD entity.

OperStatus.name: OperStatus
OperStatus.description: The current operational state of a MGMD entity.

PmIndex.name: PmIndex
PmIndex.description: The index value identifying a MGMD entity.

MjStatus.name: MjStatus
MjStatus.description: The status of a Master Join.

InterfaceType.name: InterfaceType
InterfaceType.description: The type of interface to which a join applies.

mgmdPmEntEntry.name: mgmdPmEntEntry
mgmdPmEntEntry.description: Each entry represents an instance of the MGMD Protocol Manager entity.

mgmdPmEntIndex.name: mgmdPmEntIndex
mgmdPmEntIndex.description: The index of this mgmdPmEntEntry. This is the HAF entity index passed on the entity create parameters.

mgmdPmEntAdminStatus.name: mgmdPmEntAdminStatus
mgmdPmEntAdminStatus.description: The desired administrative state of the MGMD Protocol Manager entity.

mgmdPmEntOperStatus.name: mgmdPmEntOperStatus
mgmdPmEntOperStatus.description: The current operational state of the MGMD Protocol Manager entity.

mgmdPmEntRowStatus.name: mgmdPmEntRowStatus
mgmdPmEntRowStatus.description: Used to create and delete an MGMD Protocol Manager Entity Table entry.

mgmdPmMjTable.name: mgmdPmMjTable
mgmdPmMjTable.description: This table controls which entities the MGMD Protocol Manager should join to as master. Each join is represented by a row in this table. The status of each join is represented by a read-only object within each row.

mgmdPmMjEntry.name: mgmdPmMjEntry
mgmdPmMjEntry.description: Represents a join for which the MGMD Protocol Manager is master.

mgmdPmMjEntIndex.name: mgmdPmMjEntIndex
mgmdPmMjEntIndex.description: Identifies a MGMD Protocol Manager entity.

mgmdPmMjInterfaceId.name: mgmdPmMjInterfaceId
mgmdPmMjInterfaceId.description: Identifies the interface required of this master join.

mgmdPmMjPartnerIndex.name: mgmdPmMjPartnerIndex
mgmdPmMjPartnerIndex.description: Identifies the slave entity to join with. This index is used in the join user data, to enable FTI-specific code within System Manager to select a suitable slave entity.

mgmdPmMjRowStatus.name: mgmdPmMjRowStatus
mgmdPmMjRowStatus.description: The row status for this MGMD Protocol Manager Master Join Table entry, used to create and destroy table entries.

mgmdPmMjAdminStatus.name: mgmdPmMjAdminStatus
mgmdPmMjAdminStatus.description: The administrative status of this master join, used to start and stop the join.

mgmdPmMjOperStatus.name: mgmdPmMjOperStatus
mgmdPmMjOperStatus.description: The current operational status of this master join.

mgmdPmMjJoinStatus.name: mgmdPmMjJoinStatus
mgmdPmMjJoinStatus.description: The status of the master join.

mgmdPmStaticGroupTable.name: mgmdPmStaticGroupTable
mgmdPmStaticGroupTable.description: The list of multicast groups which are statically joined on an MGMD host or router.

mgmdPmStaticGroupEntry.name: mgmdPmStaticGroupEntry
mgmdPmStaticGroupEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the mgmdPmStaticGroupTable.

mgmdPmStaticGroupEntityType.name: mgmdPmStaticGroupEntityType
mgmdPmStaticGroupEntityType.description: The entity type, host or router, that this static group will apply to.

mgmdPmStaticGroupIfIndex.name: mgmdPmStaticGroupIfIndex
mgmdPmStaticGroupIfIndex.description: The interface that is a member of the group. The interface can be either a layer 2 or 3 interface.

mgmdPmStaticGroupAddressType.name: mgmdPmStaticGroupAddressType
mgmdPmStaticGroupAddressType.description: The address type of the InetAddress variables in this table. This value applies to the mgmdPmStaticGroupAddress and mgmdPmStaticGroupSourceAddress entries.

mgmdPmStaticGroupAddress.name: mgmdPmStaticGroupAddress
mgmdPmStaticGroupAddress.description: The multicast group address to make static.

mgmdPmStaticGroupSourceAddress.name: mgmdPmStaticGroupSourceAddress
mgmdPmStaticGroupSourceAddress.description: The source of the multicast group traffic for SSM. Set to 0.0.0.0 if not using SSM.

mgmdPmStaticGroupStorageType.name: mgmdPmStaticGroupStorageType
mgmdPmStaticGroupStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row. Only the rows provisioned with nonVolatie(3) will be persistent.

mgmdPmRouterInterfaceTable.name: mgmdPmRouterInterfaceTable
mgmdPmRouterInterfaceTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the interfaces on which IGMP or MLD is enabled.

mgmdPmRouterInterfaceEntry.name: mgmdPmRouterInterfaceEntry
mgmdPmRouterInterfaceEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing an interface on which IGMP or MLD is enabled.

mgmdPmRouterInterfaceIfIndex.name: mgmdPmRouterInterfaceIfIndex
mgmdPmRouterInterfaceIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the interface for which IGMP or MLD is enabled. The table is indexed by the ifIndex value and the InetAddressType to allow for interfaces which may be configured in both IPv4 and IPv6 modes.

mgmdPmRouterInterfaceQuerierType.name: mgmdPmRouterInterfaceQuerierType
mgmdPmRouterInterfaceQuerierType.description: The address type of this interface. This entry along with the ifIndex value acts as the index to the mgmdPmRouterInterface table. A physical interface may be configured in multiple modes concurrently, e.g. in IPv4 and IPv6 modes connected to the same interface, however the traffic is considered to be logically separate.

mgmdPmRouterInterfaceQuerier.name: mgmdPmRouterInterfaceQuerier
mgmdPmRouterInterfaceQuerier.description: The address of the IGMP or MLD Querier on the IP subnet to which this interface is attached. The InetAddressType, e.g. IPv4 or IPv6, is identified by the mgmdPmRouterInterfaceQuerierType variable in the mgmdPmRouterInterface table.

mgmdPmRouterInterfaceQueryInterval.name: mgmdPmRouterInterfaceQueryInterval
mgmdPmRouterInterfaceQueryInterval.description: The frequency at which IGMP or MLD Host-Query packets are transmitted on this interface. This variable must be a non-zero value.

mgmdPmRouterInterfaceStatus.name: mgmdPmRouterInterfaceStatus
mgmdPmRouterInterfaceStatus.description: The activation of a row enables the router side of IGMP or MLD on the interface. The destruction of a row disables the router side of IGMP or MLD on the interface.

mgmdPmRouterInterfaceVersion.name: mgmdPmRouterInterfaceVersion
mgmdPmRouterInterfaceVersion.description: The version of MGMD which is running on this interface. Value 1 applies to IGMPv1 routers only. Value 2 applies To IGMPv2 and MLDv1 routers, and value 3 applies to IGMPv3 and MLDv2 routers. This object can be used to configure a router capable of running either version. For IGMP and MLD to function correctly, all routers on a LAN must be configured to run the same version on that LAN.

mgmdPmRouterInterfaceQueryMaxResponseTim.name: mgmdPmRouterInterfaceQueryMaxResponseTime
mgmdPmRouterInterfaceQueryMaxResponseTim.description: The maximum query response time advertised in MGMDv2 or v3 queries on this interface.

mgmdPmRouterInterfaceQuerierUpTime.name: mgmdPmRouterInterfaceQuerierUpTime
mgmdPmRouterInterfaceQuerierUpTime.description: The time since mgmdPmRouterInterfaceQuerier was last changed.

mgmdPmRouterInterfaceQuerierExpiryTime.name: mgmdPmRouterInterfaceQuerierExpiryTime
mgmdPmRouterInterfaceQuerierExpiryTime.description: The amount of time remaining before the Other Querier Present Timer expires. If the local system is the querier, the value of this object is zero.

mgmdPmRouterInterfaceWrongVersionQueries.name: mgmdPmRouterInterfaceWrongVersionQueries
mgmdPmRouterInterfaceWrongVersionQueries.description: The number of queries received whose IGMP or MLD version does not match the equivalent mgmdPmRouterInterfaceVersion, over the lifetime of the row entry. Both IGMP and MLD require that all routers on a LAN be configured to run the same version. Thus, if any queries are received with the wrong version, this indicates a configuration error.

mgmdPmRouterInterfaceJoins.name: mgmdPmRouterInterfaceJoins
mgmdPmRouterInterfaceJoins.description: The number of times a group membership has been added on this interface; that is, the number of times an entry for this interface has been added to the Cache Table. This object gives an indication of the amount of IGMP or MLD activity over the lifetime of the row entry.

mgmdPmRouterInterfaceProxyIfIndex.name: mgmdPmRouterInterfaceProxyIfIndex
mgmdPmRouterInterfaceProxyIfIndex.description: Some devices implement a form of IGMP or MLD proxying whereby memberships learned on the interface represented by this row, cause Host Membership Reports to be sent on the interface whose ifIndex value is given by this object. Such a device would implement the mgmdV2RouterMIBGroup only on its router interfaces (those interfaces with non-zero mgmdPmRouterInterfaceProxyIfIndex). Typically, the value of this object is 0, indicating that no proxying is being done.

mgmdPmRouterInterfaceGroups.name: mgmdPmRouterInterfaceGroups
mgmdPmRouterInterfaceGroups.description: The current number of entries for this interface in the RouterCache Table.

mgmdPmRouterInterfaceRobustness.name: mgmdPmRouterInterfaceRobustness
mgmdPmRouterInterfaceRobustness.description: The Robustness Variable allows tuning for the expected packet loss on a subnet. If a subnet is expected to be lossy, the Robustness Variable may be increased. IGMP and MLD is robust to (Robustness Variable-1) packet losses.

mgmdPmRouterInterfaceLastMembQueryIntvl.name: mgmdPmRouterInterfaceLastMembQueryIntvl
mgmdPmRouterInterfaceLastMembQueryIntvl.description: The Last Member Query Interval is the Max Response Time inserted into Group-Specific Queries sent in response to Leave Group messages, and is also the amount of time Between Group-Specific Query messages. This value may be tuned to modify the leave latency of the network. A reduced value results in reduced time to detect the loss of the last member of a group. The value of this object is irrelevant if mgmdPmRouterInterfaceVersion is 1.

mgmdPmRouterInterfaceLastMembQueryCount.name: mgmdPmRouterInterfaceLastMembQueryCount
mgmdPmRouterInterfaceLastMembQueryCount.description: Represents the number of Group-specific and Group-and-Source-specific queries sent by the router before it assumes there are no local members.

mgmdPmRouterInterfaceStartupQueryCount.name: mgmdPmRouterInterfaceStartupQueryCount
mgmdPmRouterInterfaceStartupQueryCount.description: Represents the number of Queries sent out on startup separated by the Startup Query Interval.

mgmdPmRouterInterfaceStartupQueryInterva.name: mgmdPmRouterInterfaceStartupQueryInterval
mgmdPmRouterInterfaceStartupQueryInterva.description: This variable represents the interval between General Queries sent by a Querier on startup.

mgmdPmRouterInterfaceStaticMulticastMode.name: mgmdPmRouterInterfaceStaticMulticastMode
mgmdPmRouterInterfaceStaticMulticastMode.description: If true then this interface will only be able to join groups statically. All querier and dynamic join functionality will be disabled.

mgmdPmRouterInterfaceBackupProxyIfIndex.name: mgmdPmRouterInterfaceBackupProxyIfIndex
mgmdPmRouterInterfaceBackupProxyIfIndex.description: Some devices implement a form of IGMP or MLD proxying whereby memberships learned on the interface represented by this row, cause Host Membership Reports to be sent on the interface whose ifIndex value is given by this object. Such a device would implement the mgmdV2RouterMIBGroup only on its router interfaces (those interfaces with non-zero mgmdPmRouterInterfaceProxyIfIndex). If a proxy interface is defined for an interface a secondary backup proxy interface can be configured for failover operation.

mgmdPmRouterInterfaceAccessList.name: mgmdPmRouterInterfaceAccessList
mgmdPmRouterInterfaceAccessList.description: The access list number for filtering multicast group join requests by hosts. Set to 0 for no filtering. Only Standard ACLs (in the range 1-99) are supported.

mgmdPmRouterInterfaceIgmpResetCounts.name: mgmdPmRouterInterfaceIgmpResetCounts
mgmdPmRouterInterfaceIgmpResetCounts.description: Reset the send and receive counts and intervals

mgmdPmRouterInterfaceIgmpCountIntvl.name: mgmdPmRouterInterfaceIgmpCountIntvl
mgmdPmRouterInterfaceIgmpCountIntvl.description: The time interval in seconds that IGMP receive and send packets were counted

mgmdPmRouterInterfaceIgmpRcvCount.name: mgmdPmRouterInterfaceIgmpRcvCount
mgmdPmRouterInterfaceIgmpRcvCount.description: The number of IGMP packets received during the count interval

mgmdPmRouterInterfaceIgmpSendCount.name: mgmdPmRouterInterfaceIgmpSendCount
mgmdPmRouterInterfaceIgmpSendCount.description: The number of IGMP packets sent during the count interval

mgmdPmRouterInterfaceProxyAutoSwitchback.name: mgmdPmRouterInterfaceProxyAutoSwitchback
mgmdPmRouterInterfaceProxyAutoSwitchback.description: If set to true then auto-switchback mode is enabled. If set to false then auto-switchback mode is disabled.
